6\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Explosive devices set off fires on signalling infrastructure on three lines going into Paris.\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.859663041411362e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tbrowser thatsupports HTML5 \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvideo  Up Next  Lines from cities such as Lille in the north, Bordeaux in the west and Strasbourg in the east were hit.\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3465530784053782e-18, \"text\": \"JavaScript\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\"}, {\"begin\": 1274, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7283958654824774e-16, \"text\": \"HTML5\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\"}, {\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Music_Up_Next\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Up Next\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Music_Up_Next\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Music_Up_Next\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille-Europe_station\", \"score\": 0.8934100078917919, \"rank\": 0.11930688444196191, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille-Europe_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille-Europe_station\"}, {\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"score\": 0.9999999794376893, \"rank\": 2.056213590389852e-08, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\"}, {\"begin\": 1375, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg\", \"score\": 0.9960901329023021, \"rank\": 0.003925214163611839, \"text\": \"Strasbourg\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gare Montparnasse in Paris saw the biggest disruptions, with hundreds of people left stranded there in the hours after.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1409, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_Montparnasse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gare Montparnasse\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_Montparnasse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_Montparnasse\"}, {\"begin\": 1430, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.859663041411362e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SNCF warned that delays and cancellations will continue on these routes 'at least over the weekend'.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Services were gradually returning to normal on Saturday morning after engineers worked overnight to repair signal stations and cables\\u00a0damaged by fire.\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 24 hours later, mystery remains about who was behind the attacks - but a number of security gaps have been exposed in the aftermath.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There has been no immediate claim of responsibility, and Prime Minister Gabriel Attal stressed that it was too early to speculate about who might be behind them.\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'What we know, what we see, is that this operation was prepared, coordinated, that nerve centres were targeted, which shows a certain knowledge of the network to know where to strike,' he said.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris prosecutor's office said that an investigation would be overseen by its organised crime office, with the anti-terrorist sub-directorate (SDAT), a branch of the judicial police that typically monitors far-left, far-right and radical environmental groups, coordinating investigations.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2290, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.859663041411362e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nato secretary-general Jens Stoltenberg said in June that the alliance had seen several examples of 'sabotage, of arson attempts' by Russia.\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2713, \"end\": 2719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999840838, \"rank\": 1.5867316344943593e-11, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is no indication that the Kremlin is actually behind the attack.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2758, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999672720067503, \"rank\": 3.2729064555882935e-05, \"text\": \"Kremlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least 800,000 people were impacted by the chaos in the last 24 hours, including Eurostar passengers.\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.470199070541447e-14, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SNCF had urged customers not to travel to the station on Friday morning as most trains were either cancelled or heavily delayed.\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Eurostar\\u00a0said it would axe a quarter of all services and asked people to postpone their travel where possible on Friday.\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3044, \"end\": 3052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.470199070541447e-14, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One in four trains on Friday, Saturday, and Sunday are cancelled, and those which are actually running face between one and two hour delays.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those impacted can change their booking to a different date and time, free of charge; cancel their booking for an e-voucher redeemable on any train within the next year; or get a full refund for free.\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eurostar said: 'Due to coordinated acts of vandalism in France, affecting the high-speed line between Paris and Lille, all high-speed trains going to and coming from Paris are being diverted via the classic line today Friday, July 26.\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3510, \"end\": 3518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.470199070541447e-14, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}, {\"begin\": 3566, \"end\": 3572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999997344220335, \"rank\": 2.381936635795854e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3612, \"end\": 3617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.859663041411362e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3622, \"end\": 3627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille-Europe_station\", \"score\": 0.8934100078917919, \"rank\": 0.11930688444196191, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille-Europe_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille-Europe_station\"}, {\"begin\": 3676, \"end\": 3681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.859663041411362e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'This extends the journey time by around an hour and a half.\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several trains have been cancelled.\", \"from\": 3807, \"to\": 3842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Eurostar's teams are fully mobilised in stations, in the call centres, and onboard to assist and ensure our passengers are fully informed.\", \"from\": 3844, \"to\": 3983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3845, \"end\": 3853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.470199070541447e-14, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Customers are being informed via email, SMS and on Eurostar.com.'\", \"from\": 3985, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4026, \"end\": 4029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SMS\", \"score\": 0.9355229994984683, \"rank\": 0.06892080743735737, \"text\": \"SMS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SMS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SMS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Russian national with suspected links to espionage networks was arrested in Paris over a plot to 'destabilise' the Olympics earlier this week.\", \"from\": 4053, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.6969711119245304, \"rank\": 0.4190693998776818, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4131, \"end\": 4136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.859663041411362e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": 